race.comment: GO COMMANDO (4) met with strong support on debut a fortnight ago and dug deep to the prize over 1175m at Albury. Promising three-year-old who is by Savabeel so this longer trip can only help his cause. LUNA JET (6) has found the line strongly to just miss the placings at all three runs this prep in shorter races. Crying out for 1400m - watch for her in the final stages. KILTIKI (5) returned in good order at Coonabarabran last start, edged out in a three-way thriller over this distance. Building a nice 1400m record and makes his own luck up front. Right in the mix. SUNDAY (7) led all the way and just prevailed in the same race as KILTIKI at Coonabarabran recently, her first win after 11 tries. Took a while to get off the mark but might give them something to catch again. KICKOFF (8) caught the eye at Kempsey last start and will appreciate the extra 150m today.
